Sure, here's a simple example of a basic website using HTML and CSS. This example includes a header, navigation menu, and a content section. You can use this as a starting point and expand upon it as needed:

html
Copy code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Simple Website</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #333;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px 0;
        }

        nav {
            background-color: #444;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px 0;
        }

        nav a {
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #fff;
            margin: 0 20px;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <a href="#">Home</a>
        <a href="#">About</a>
        <a href="#">Services</a>
        <a href="#">Contact</a>
    </nav>

    <div class="container">
        <h2>Welcome to Our Website</h2>
        <p>This is a simple website created using HTML and CSS.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
